    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love these scones and was thrilled that I had all of the ingredients on hand.  I ended up using an unsweetened vanilla almond milk, raisins, and a dash of cinnamon in the batter and they turned out flaky and lovely.  I also sprinkled the tops with a bit of raw (turbinado) sugar before baking.</></>Next time I&#8217;ll try using real dairy milk&#8211; maybe 1% to get a bit more richness.</p>
    </div>

